      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
      <dateline>PITTSBURGH, March 26</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mario Lemieux had five goals and two assists to dominate his first game against Wayne Gretzky in more than three years and lead the Pittsburgh Penguins  to an 8-4 victory over the St. Louis Blues tonight.</p>
        <p>Lemieux, playing his first game since his wife delivered a baby on Sunday, got his sixth hat trick of the season and 37th of his career. It was his third five-goal game.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Mario Lemieux had five goals and two assists to dominate his first game against Wayne Gretzky in more than three years and lead the Pittsburgh Penguins  to an 8-4 victory over the St. Louis Blues tonight.</p>
        <p>Lemieux, playing his first game since his wife delivered a baby on Sunday, got his sixth hat trick of the season and 37th of his career. It was his third five-goal game.</p>
        <p>Lemieux's wife, Nathalie, gave birth to their third child on Sunday. The 2-pound-5-ounce boy was three months early and is expected to remain on a respirator for a few days.</p>
      </block>
